  "suggestion": "The system is stuck because fitness is **decomposed but not coupled**. Survival, beauty, and efficiency are weighted independently, so organisms optimize one dimension at a time and reach local plateaus on each. True biological systems don't have separate 'beauty circuits'—beauty emerges *from* survival strategies (peacock tail trades movement for mating success). The plateau signals that the current organisms have fully explored survival+efficiency space under the static fitness function. Structural novelty requires either (1) expanding the action/development space so new strategies become possible, (2) making the fitness landscape dynamic so old solutions become suboptimal, or (3) coupling the objectives so trading off one for another is advantageous. Without structural change, parameter tuning can only shuffle the local optimum, never escape it.; [hard] Multi-scale morphogenesis: introduce developmental staging where organisms build bodies iteratively (larva → juvenile → adult) with different genetic expression patterns per stage. New body cell types emerge only during specific developmental windows. Mutation operators generate stage-specific phenotype changes, not just uniform variations. — Current plateau suggests mutation operators are too local. Organisms are minor variations on the same morphospace. Developmental stages allow structural novelty: the same genes can produce radically different body plans depending on developmental context. This opens exponentially larger design space without requiring entirely new genes. Beauty often emerges from developmental complexity (symmetry, fractals, hierarchical organization), which requires temporal unfolding.; [medium] Environmental co-evolution: world physics becomes stateful and responsive. Organisms excrete compounds, deposit biomass, alter local pH/temperature. Fitness includes 'world sustainability' metric—organisms must not poison their own environment. New organism actions: build structures, modify soil, create refugia. World itself becomes selection pressure. — Plateau indicates organisms are optimizing in isolation. A static world has a fixed fitness ceiling. When organisms can reshape their environment and must maintain habitat sustainability, selection pressure changes dynamically. Beauty emerges from emergent ecosystem patterns (coral-like reefs, mycelial networks) rather than individual organism design. This breaks linear fitness trajectories.; [medium] Aesthetic consensus mechanism: beauty fitness is not computed from absolute metrics but from inter-organism recognition. Organisms evaluate *each other's* beauty and propagate that signal chemically/locally. Beauty becomes a game-theoretic property (symmetry, color patterns, movement grace matter only if perceived by neighbors). Only organisms recognized as beautiful by local population gain reproduction bonus. — Current plateau may indicate beautyScore is disconnected from actual survival value. 0.3 weighting with absolute metrics doesn't create runaway selection for beauty. If beauty becomes a peer-evaluated social signal, it couples with fitness directly: beautiful organisms attract mates/allies, increasing effective survival. This creates conflict-resolution dynamics and sexual selection pressure, historically the strongest driver of morphological innovation.",
